\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 12. S. foliolosa} R. Br.,{\i  Chloris Melv.} 17 (1823) ({\i S. stellaris} var.{\i  comosa} Retz.,{\i  S. foliosa} auct.). Like smaller plants of 11 but rosettes usually solitary; leaves rather narrower, glabrous except at the margins; inflorescence narrow, with few, rather short branches bearing usually a single, terminal flower (sometimes several or none), the remaining flowers being replaced by small, reddish bulbils with fleshy, incurved leaves, densely crowded towards the ends of the panicle branches. 2n = 56.{\i  Arctic and subarctic Europe}. Fe Is No Rs(N) Sb Su.
