\pard\f0\fs28 Sect. COTYLEA Tausch ({\i Miscopetalum} (Haw.) Sternb.). Evergreen perennials with underground rhizome or stock. Leaves alternate, mostly basal, long-petiolate, entire to crenate, dentate or slightly lobed. Flowering stem leafy; flowers in a panicle. Sepals erect or patent; petals white, usually with red or yellow spots. Ovary superior.
\par

