\pard\f0\fs28  ({\b b}) Subsp. {\b chrysosplenifolia} (Boiss.) D.A. Webb in Jordanov, {\i Fl. Rep. Pop. Bulg.}{\b  4}: 658 (1970) ({\i S. chrysosplenifolia} Boiss.): Lamina of basal leaves decurrent along the petiole, which is broadened at the top; margin of lamina not cartilaginous, usually ciliate. 2n = 22. •{\i  S. part of Balkan peninsula and Aegean region}.
