\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 14. S. taygetea} Boiss. & Heldr. in Boiss.,{\i  Diagn. Pl. Or. Nov.}{\b  2}({\b 10}): 19 (1849). Like {\b 13}({\b a}) but smaller (stem seldom 20 cm); basal leaves 15-25 mm wide, with 5-9 broad, shallow crenations, or subacute teeth; cauline leaves few and small; petals 7-9 mm, white with numerous red spots; ovary crimson. 2n = 22. •{\i  Exposed mountain rocks. S. & W. Greece, Albania, Crna Gora}. Al Gr Ju.
